  "text": "where Q is the graviphoton charge Q ∼ D/q 0 . This is true before adding α ′ or g s corrections, and all the simple candidate corrections one can write down (such as powers of F and its derivatives, for example those which appear in the MMMS equation [CITATION_1] ), preserve Eq. (2.5). While there are still F 2 sources in Eq. (2.4), one can now check that these are canceled by terms coming from the space-time dependence of radius R 10 of 11th dimension (in M theory) or the dilaton (in IIa). We omit the explicit check, instead pointing out that since the sources are constructed only from the metric tensor on X, they can at most add a cosmological constant term in Eq. (2.4), leading to a Kähler-Einstein metric. However, standard arguments imply that a solution exists only if this term is proportional to c 1 (X), which is zero for a CY.",
